s identity, though in Lesotho, for example, some individuals were cross when they didn\rquote t see themselves identified by their names.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid9637019  Other times, a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid4722222\charrsid4722222 lthough families are disguised, local people may be identified from the stories by others in the area.  To deal with this problem she uses \'93}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\ul\insrsid4722222\charrsid4722222 composite case studies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4722222\charrsid4722222 \'94.  This is done by taking pieces from various individuals as a kind of \'93for instance\'94
 (a kind of fictionalising) to make up a case study.  She believes this is justified if you are very clear about what you are doing.  Ultimately, she believes that \'93whatever we do, the ethics of it are never absolutely clear because you are taking st
uff from people\'94.  She doesn\rquote t believe \'93ethically pure\'94 makes any sense, because when we ask for informed consent, people aren\rquote t always sure about what we are asking them for.  
\par 
\par She spoke of the challenges that arise from doing collaborative research, and
 the need to be very clear that everyone is looking at the same thing instead of emphasising their own disciplines.  Conducting collaboratively with multidisciplinary researchers can results in conflicts along the way.  This can be very rich experience if
 everyone brings to the project their own expertise and takes responsibility for communicating what they are doing with the others.  
\par 
\par Collaborative and multidisciplinary work requires one to put in time, to listen a lot, which is a difficult talent to deve
lop, and collaborative work requires similar listening skills that are required when listening to your informants/respondents.  A major drawback to collaborative approach is the extra time and patience that it requires.  
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid4722222\charrsid4722222 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4722222\charrsid4722222 The first London study was about 
the dynamics of a mixed population, looking at how people get by in difficult circumstances, the strategies which they use, how amazing they are in terms of sheer survival.  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid2036892 Although each of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4722222\charrsid4722222  her research }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid2036892 projects }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4722222\charrsid4722222 had its own stated objective, the essential concern was usually about \'93How do\'85 What are the options in this\'85
 area or in this circumstance?   Who takes up the options? How do people manage a livelihood, and what do they regard as a decent livelihood? These include her work with the Kampala women and her work in Turin.
\par 
\par Her work is not simply for the sake of advancing knowledge, but they are \'93applied\'94 or \'93action\'94 and \'93practice-oriented\'94.   She believes that each of her work has a potential for practical contribution or a potential policy contribution.  

\par 
\par In her current book, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\insrsid4722222\charrsid4722222 The Capability of Places: A Classification of Local Systems }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4722222\charrsid4722222 
(in progress), she makes a distinction between \'93method\'94 and \'93methodology\'94.  
\par 
\par The \'93ology\'94 side is very significant.  It\rquote s the argument.  The \'93ology\'94 is addressing issues such as \'93Why am I doing this?  What\rquote s the reasoning behind it?\'94  \'93What\rquote s the theoretical frame?\'94  
\par 
\par Methods are the strategies (not the argument).  Having decided on the theoretical frame and the questions that you want to pursue, you then ask, \'93How can I find this out?\'94  You then begin to develop methods, or strategies to address \'93}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid4722222\charrsid4722222 How}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid4722222\charrsid4722222  can I find that out?\'94 \'93Do I make network maps?\'94  \'93Do I make an interview schedule?
\'94 or \'93What do I need?\'94  The kind of method (strategies) you can use will be determined on the basis of what resources you have, what the problem is, what the setting is etc.  Behind the methods should be a fairly developed statement of the \'93
ology\'94 side. 
\par 
\par She hasn\rquote t archived anything from any of her projects, though she thinks some of the Zambian material may have been archived.  She keeps a lot of her fieldwork material from her various projects in a filing cabinet at UCL.
\par 
\par She doesn\rquote t have any strong feelings either way about archiving, but not sure how much one gets out of it, though some of the material can be fascinating.  
\par 
\par She mentioned the ethics involved in research and the importance of censoring certain information that might be deemed damaging to the informer.  In whi
ch case putting a 30-year embargo on the data might be the alternative.  She believes archiving can be useful if indeed the material is revisited by people working in applied research with political relevance.  
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15620469 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid15620469\charrsid4722222 The outcome for the Battersea project was n
ot action, but an insight into racial politics which revealed that race doesn\rquote t always count.  In some parts of London race counts but in some parts it doesn\rquote t.  
