She finds it easier to think of what she is pleased about with regards to parenting.  She is pleased that all her children seem to be comfortable in whatever kind of society they find themselves without fe
eling personally threatened, and she feels that she has contributed to that. 
\par 
\par Although she thinks working and raising children is \lquote hard work\rquote , she believes that if she didn\rquote t have children she\rquote d be a \lquote lesser anthropologist\rquote , and if she didn\rquote t have anthropology she might have \lquote 
over-mothered\rquote  by too much watching and analysing her children.
\par 
\par Looking back she finds it difficult to imagine how she managed raising her children and her heavy workload simultaneously.  
